      vibe: "Liège in August: warm, chaotic and genuinely joyful. Micro rewards people who turn up without a plan and let the programme surprise them. Electronic weirdness on Friday, post-punk and noise on Saturday, avant-garde and world music closing on Sunday.",
      sounds: "Deliberately genre-defiant. 2026 lineup spans Dopplereffekt (US/DE electro legends), Cio d'Or (DE deep techno), Atom TM (DE experimental), Catnapp (AR/DE), The Zawose Queens (TZ), Deadletter and M(h)aol (UK/IE post-punk), Los Sara Fontan (ES), Bathing Suits, GEE TEE, Sartorius Drum Ensemble, Vanligt Folk and strong Belgian representation throughout.",
      doNotMiss: "Sunday's closing stretch — The Zawose Queens from Tanzania alongside Atom TM and Cio d'Or in the same afternoon is the kind of programming you simply don't see elsewhere.",
      tip: "Liège-Guillemins is one of Belgium's main train hubs — direct connections from Brussels, Cologne, Paris and Amsterdam. The venue is in the Outremeuse district, walkable from the station.",
